c: 48
v: 11
t: "The wandering Bedouin Arabs, those who (deliberately) lagged behind, will (no doubt) say to you, \"Our assets and our families kept us busy. So pray (to Allah) for our forgiveness.\" With their lips they utter that which is (just) not there in their hearts. Say, \"Does anyone have even the slightest ability to stop Allah, if He intends to hurt you _ or help you? Allah is well Aware of what you do"